title: Coomacarrea
text:
Coomacarrea () is a 772 m (2,533 ft) <a href="mountain">mountain</a> in <a href="County%20Kerry">County Kerry</a>, <a href="Republic%20of%20Ireland">Ireland</a>.
Geography.
The mountain is part of the <a href="Mountains%20of%20the%20Iveragh%20Peninsula">Mountains of the Iveragh Peninsula</a> and is the highest peak of the <a href="Glenbeigh%20Horseshoe">Glenbeigh Horseshoe</a>.
